WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.060
I am aware that I am inhaling, I am aware that I am exhaling, I am following my

2
00:00:05.060 --> 00:00:10.220
breath, I become aware of my body, I relax my body, I generate

3
00:00:10.220 --> 00:00:16.600
a feeling of joy, I generate a feeling of happiness in

4
00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:17.000
the present.

5
00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:22.020
I become aware of my pain, I embrace my pain, I take care of it.

6
00:00:22.900 --> 00:00:27.240
It's important to have good motivation when you're going to start meditating.

7
00:00:28.067 --> 00:00:33.127
will present you with obstacles. The first obstacle you

8
00:00:33.127 --> 00:00:35.487
will encounter is laziness. It will

9
00:00:35.487 --> 00:00:40.007
bring you a second subtlety, which is called active laziness. I was doing a

10
00:00:40.007 --> 00:00:45.527
lot of things except going to meditate. A third laziness that still arises is

11
00:00:45.527 --> 00:00:46.827
giving up. But

12
00:00:46.827 --> 00:00:52.207
then you tell yourself no, ultimately it's not for me. The antidote

13
00:00:52.207 --> 00:00:53.527
is to find a just motivation.

14
00:00:54.467 --> 00:00:56.067
This motivation must be

15
00:00:56.135 --> 00:00:58.315
not only for you, but also for others.

16
00:00:58.915 --> 00:01:01.315
The second real obstacle you will encounter,

17
00:01:02.035 --> 00:01:03.655
is that when you learn to meditate,

18
00:01:03.735 --> 00:01:06.755
initially, there is a methodology in learning.

19
00:01:07.315 --> 00:01:10.975
The obstacle you will encounter is the complete forgetting of what needs to be done.

20
00:01:11.675 --> 00:01:13.295
At one point, I was meditating,

21
00:01:13.495 --> 00:01:14.895
well, I thought I was meditating,

22
00:01:15.395 --> 00:01:18.315
I was sitting there, ultimately, I was dreaming quite a bit.

23
00:01:18.795 --> 00:01:21.315
I understood that meditation is a training of the mind.

24
00:01:21.635 --> 00:01:24.095
It comes from a very ancient etymology that means...

25
00:01:24.863 --> 00:01:27.303
Truly learning to discover one's own functioning.

26
00:01:27.803 --> 00:01:30.263
You're not always well when you meditate, but that's okay.

27
00:01:30.363 --> 00:01:32.983
I learn to recognize, to train my mind.

28
00:01:33.203 --> 00:01:37.003
And the antidote, which I think is very interesting for us in the practice of meditation,

29
00:01:37.283 --> 00:01:39.223
is attention, it's mindfulness.

30
00:01:39.703 --> 00:01:43.603
Discovering this energy that is in your mind, this energy that is concentration,

31
00:01:43.983 --> 00:01:48.003
and which will gradually open you to another energy which is the deep vision of things.

32
00:01:48.163 --> 00:01:49.163
But you have to go little by little.

33
00:01:49.343 --> 00:01:52.143
It's like when you enter a space or on the walls.

34
00:01:52.270 --> 00:01:54.170
There are secrets that can be revealed.

35
00:01:54.470 --> 00:01:56.770
I enter with a candle, and the candle is your mind.

36
00:01:57.250 --> 00:02:01.630
Initially, the candle moves like this, which means there's not really any brightness.

37
00:02:01.770 --> 00:02:06.670
But if through the practice of your meditation, the base, you learn to completely stabilize the flame,

38
00:02:06.870 --> 00:02:11.530
a kind of luminous halo appears, a kind of clarity emerges.

39
00:02:12.890 --> 00:02:14.190
Well, it's a bit the same thing.

40
00:02:14.370 --> 00:02:19.430
If you really manage to stabilize your mind, all of a sudden you will perceive a kind of

41
00:02:19.430 --> 00:02:20.270
luminous clarity.

42
00:02:20.338 --> 00:02:25.438
that appears in one's mind. This clarity leads you to deep vision.

43
00:02:25.878 --> 00:02:26.678
You have to learn

44
00:02:26.678 --> 00:02:31.858
to stabilize the mind because it's a whole work of stabilization. So

45
00:02:31.858 --> 00:02:32.258
it's learning

46
00:02:32.258 --> 00:02:37.078
to develop this clarity of mind first through the energy of mindfulness,

47
00:02:37.938 --> 00:02:43.138
the energy of concentration and the energy of deep vision.

48
00:02:43.998 --> 00:02:44.578
You have

49
00:02:44.578 --> 00:02:47.658
to train. Everyone can have access to this.